											<h2 class="entry-title">About</h2>
					
					<div class="entry-content">
						<h3>Abstract</h3>
<p>Effective communication between patients and their clinicians during clinical encounters has a positive impact on health outcomes. Technology has the potential to help transform this synchronous interaction, but researchers are still at early stages of developing interventions to assess and improve patient-clinician communication. In this workshop, we envision opening up a dialogue among researchers and clinicians who wish to discuss directions for future research in this domain. In particular, the workshop will focus on exploring how technologies available today, as well as projected for the future, can support the needs of clinicians and patients engaging in synchronous communication.</p>
